        "text": "@CryptoA45858295 @soigomaa In the classic Monty Haul problem, your odds of winning are 1/3 if you don't switch and 2/3 if you switch. In the problem Marilyn was asked about, your odds are 1/3 if you don't switch and can be literally anything from 0% to 100% if you switch.",
